 <center> 
  <h1><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">Requirements (IC Cards)</font></h1> 
 
</center> 
<body>
<p><font size="4" face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">Given this discussion of 
  how this system should work, let us break the requirements of the system down 
  into IC cards. These IC cards will be used in the next phase to determine the 
  relational graph.</font></p>
<p><font size="4" face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">This system will consist 
  of the following Index Cell cards:</font></p>
<p align="center"><img src="images/main_ic_card.jpg" width="469" height="268"></p>
<p><font size="4" face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">The main manager IC is the 
  starting point for the system. This IC sends activate messages to other ICs 
  to inform them that they should become live.</font></p>
<p align="center"><font size="4" face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><img src="images/desktop_ic_card.jpg" width="469" height="268"></font></p>
<p align="center"><font size="4" face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><img src="images/desktop_ic_card2.jpg" width="469" height="268"></font></p>
<p><font size="4" face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">The desktop IC will either 
  send a data request message to a track IC, crossing IC, or both. The message 
  is intended to request the current state from that IC. The Other IC's Task sections 
  above indicate the nature of the states.</font></p>
</body>
